lastHealthUpdate.message: Released.
In dev progress as part of phase II. Almost complete as of 3/19.

Spoke with Masley and Jaayden - Good to commit to a condtional parameter demo for the in-person VTAC on March 25th.

From that call

  • Planning to develop form processing component in a way that's detached from the control plane
  • This will make POC a lot faster and the demo more "mockable"
  • This also streamlines debugging
    • Rather than create template -> push -> create workspace -> see form
    • `npm run workspaceformdev` -> see forms from terraform template
    • Better for: iteration on the backend, documentation updates, error testing
  • If the component containing parameters (a subset of the workspace creation form) can be rendered independently, we can throw it in a mock frame for the demonstration
  • What will the demo contain?
    • Conditional parameters
    • Coder provider data
This is dependent on the dev containers rework. We are aiming on having to have a prototype/design/RFC in mind by the end of H1 but unsure if we can deliver the policy engine in H1.

Dynamic Parameters will release in July as Beta, with an opt-in per template.

Users go to the settings page for a given template to enable dynamic parameters. After a few months in Beta, Dynamic parameters will be the default behavior for workspace creation.
